    "department": "GTM",
    "description": "ABOUT US\n\nParallel is a web infrastructure company. Our products are used by leading businesses in sales, marketing, insurance, and coding to build best-in-class AI agents with flexible and powerful programmatic access to the web.\n\nWe've raised $130 million from Kleiner Perkins, Index Ventures, Spark Capital, Khosla Ventures, First Round, and Terrain to build the web for AIs. We're forming a world-class team of engineers, designers, marketers, sellers, researchers, and operational experts to achieve our mission.\n\nThe Role\nWe're hiring our first GTM Ops + Enablement Lead to build the operating system for how Parallel sells, onboards, and scales. You'll own the systems, playbooks, and processes that make our GTM team effective, while building the foundation that scales with us.\n\nOur buyers are engineers and technical leaders at the most ambitious AI companies in the world. Our sales cycles involve evaluations, deep technical discovery, and collaborative deployment. You'll work at the intersection of GTM, Product, and Engineering to ensure our team can confidently sell, deploy, and expand a category-defining product.\n\nWhat You'll Do\nGTM Operations\n\n - Design and optimize sales processes across the GTM team to improve productivity and performance\n\n - Own and build the GTM tech stack—evaluate, deploy, and integrate tools that fit an AI-native motion (we don't assume Salesforce is the answer)\n\n - Build scalable workflows for lead routing, account assignment, and deal management\n\n - Maintain dashboards and reporting for pipeline health, forecasts, and performance\n\n - Partner with GTM leadership on territory design, account reviews, and planning cycles\n\n - Ensure data accuracy and accessibility across systems—be the source of truth\n\nGTM Enablement\n\n - Build enablement from zero: establish the charter, operating model, and priorities\n\n - Design and run onboarding programs that ramp new hires quickly in a technical, API-first sales environment\n\n - Create field-ready playbooks for our sales motion—technical evaluations, PoCs, enterprise cycles, and expansions\n\n - Codify best practices from successful deals and turn them into repeatable motions\n\n - Translate Parallel's technical capabilities into clear value propositions the team can deliver\n\n - Create feedback loops from the field into Product and GTM leadership\n\n\nLIFE AT PARALLEL\n\nOur team works fully in-person, between our Palo Alto HQ and San Francisco office. We’re a flat, talent-dense organization dedicated to solving technical and creative problems.\n\nWe seek like-minded individuals who share our passion for applying science, creativity, and consistency to big and complex problems with equally big outcomes. These are our values:\n\n - Own customer impact: It’s on us to ensure real-world outcomes for our customers.\n\n - Obsess over craft: Perfect every detail because quality compounds.\n\n - Accelerate change: Ship fast, adapt faster, and move frontier ideas into production.\n\n - Create win-wins: Creatively turn trade-offs into upside.\n\n - Make high-conviction bets: Try and fail. But succeed an unfair amount.\n\n\nCOMPENSATION \u0026 BENEFITS\n\n - Competitive salary\n\n - Generous equity\n\n - Visa sponsorships\n\n - 401K plans\n\n - Daily lunch \u0026 office snacks\n\n - Dinner at the office\n\n - Unlimited vacation\n\n - Caltrain pass reimbursement",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
